<a  name="algorithmn"></a>
<div class="content-section-a">

    <div class="container">
        <h2>Matching Algorithm</h2>
        <hr>
        <p>
            The Matching Algorithmn is based on four personality traits that dogs and humans are matched over.
            When registering, the user is promted to answer questions that give the user scores from one to five for those traits.
            When matching traits of energy, confidence and focus between dogs and users, users will find dogs with scores that equal theirs, albeit with a plus or minus one margin.
            An example of the code that reflects this would be:
                <blockquote>if( (user.energy - dog[i].energy >= -1) && (user.energy - dog[i].energy <= 1) ...</blockquote>
            This would only accept match between a dog and user which had a equal energy scores with a margin of one.
            <br>
            The Independence trait however, is the opposite, with dogs that are higly dependent being best matched with independent people. The code used is:
                <blockquote>(user.independence + dog[i].independence >= 5) && (user.independence + dog[i].independence <= 7))</blockquote>
            This accepets matches between users and dogs where they are on different sides of the 1 to 5 scale, or indeed both in the middle.
        </p>
    </div>

</div>

