    <div class="container">
    <h2>Architecture</h2>
    <hr>
    <p>The site uses two different database collections, one collection is for the human users of the website called 'accounts' whereas the second collection is the collection of dogs that the users are able to be matched with, this collection is called 'dogs'. This was the most simple implementation we came up with regarding the adoption of dogs as it is easy to compare the energy, confidence, focus and independence the users chose with those of the dogs. The simple design and layout of our site favours the users usability, making them able to find their matching dogs quickly so they are able to adopt as soon as possible.</p>
    </div>

